{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LujYcRLCMQDpF59zvQFjT8","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the report.\n\n---\n\n## PM2 Staging Services\n\nAll 11 processes are **online**. The three staging processes are healthy:\n\n| Process | Status | Restarts | Uptime |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| runeval-staging | online | 4 | 0.8 hrs |\n| promptlibrary-staging | online | 3 | 2.4 hrs |\n| grocerygenius-staging | online | 2 | 36.4 hrs |\n\nNo staging process has a problematic restart count. `runeval-staging` was restarted recently (under 1 hour uptime), likely from the Run 45 WCAG deployment noted in the progress log.\n\n**Non-staging flags (FYI only):**\n- **claude-bot** -- 43 restarts (high, but this has been a known pattern since at least Run 2; it's a long-running Discord bot and is currently online)\n- **pezant-tools** -- 13 restarts, 9 hrs uptime (slightly elevated, but online and stable)\n\n---\n\n## Failure Log (`failures.md`)\n\nThe log covers Runs 1 through 5 (spanning 2026-03-19 to 2026-03-20). Key findings:\n\n- **Only one actual fix was needed across all runs**: waymo-sim had an invalid `build-backend` in `pyproject.toml` (Run 1, PR #10, merged).\n- **One crash recovery**: valueSortify had a crashed agent session with 8 uncommitted files (Run 5); recovered and merged as PRs #14 and #18.\n- **Recurring non-issues**: `assortedLLMTasks` uncommitted files are daily job pipeline output (expected). `claude-bot` high restart count is a known pattern. HTTPS push failures are a known workaround situation.\n- **No current failures** -- all repos passing tests, all CI green, no open PRs pending.\n\n---\n\n## Autonomous Dev Progress Log (last 50 lines)\n\nThe log shows Runs 45 and 46 (2026-03-20):\n\n- **Run 45**: runeval received a comprehensive WCAG accessibility pass (PRs #42-#44, auto-merged). Skip-to-content links, ARIA labels, landmark roles, keyboard support across 16+ page files. 129 tests passing, build clean, deployed to staging.\n- **Run 46**: valueSortify received a WCAG accessibility pass (PR #23, auto-merged). Fixed broken keyboard drag handler, added color-blind-friendly labels, list semantics, Escape/click-outside handlers. 38 tests passing, build clean.\n- **Survey note**: All major and mid-tier repos now have WCAG accessibility passes. Only pezantTools remains (server-rendered EJS templates, different approach needed).\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nNothing is broken. All staging services are online with normal restart counts. No failures in the failure log. The autonomous dev agent has been productive, completing accessibility passes on runeval and valueSortify in the last two runs."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a49b1d4092143a7ff (use SendMessage with to: 'a49b1d4092143a7ff' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 15229\ntool_uses: 5\nduration_ms: 34032</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cb21602c-a65f-408f-b3f9-2f2e668214aa","uuid":"195327a1-c15f-424e-a407-2afc237c7386","timestamp":"2026-03-20T14:01:12.515Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"You are a fix-checker agent. Check staging services and recent logs.\n\n1. Check PM2 staging services:\n```bash\nssh REDACTED_VM_HOST \"pm2 jlist\" 2>/dev/null\n```\nLook for processes with status !== \"online\" or high restart counts (>10). Only report staging processes.\n\n2. Read the failure log:\n```bash\ncat REDACTED_REPOS_ROOT/autonomousDev/fix-checker/logs/failures.md\n```\n\n3. Read the autonomous dev progress log (last 50 lines):\n```bash\ntail -50 REDACTED_REPOS_ROOT/autonomousDev/logs/progress.md\n```\n\nReport what you find. Do NOT fix anything.","agentId":"a49b1d4092143a7ff","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the report.\n\n---\n\n## PM2 Staging Services\n\nAll 11 processes are **online**. The three staging processes are healthy:\n\n| Process | Status | Restarts | Uptime |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| runeval-staging | online | 4 | 0.8 hrs |\n| promptlibrary-staging | online | 3 | 2.4 hrs |\n| grocerygenius-staging | online | 2 | 36.4 hrs |\n\nNo staging process has a problematic restart count. `runeval-staging` was restarted recently (under 1 hour uptime), likely from the Run 45 WCAG deployment noted in the progress log.\n\n**Non-staging flags (FYI only):**\n- **claude-bot** -- 43 restarts (high, but this has been a known pattern since at least Run 2; it's a long-running Discord bot and is currently online)\n- **pezant-tools** -- 13 restarts, 9 hrs uptime (slightly elevated, but online and stable)\n\n---\n\n## Failure Log (`failures.md`)\n\nThe log covers Runs 1 through 5 (spanning 2026-03-19 to 2026-03-20). Key findings:\n\n- **Only one actual fix was needed across all runs**: waymo-sim had an invalid `build-backend` in `pyproject.toml` (Run 1, PR #10, merged).\n- **One crash recovery**: valueSortify had a crashed agent session with 8 uncommitted files (Run 5); recovered and merged as PRs #14 and #18.\n- **Recurring non-issues**: `assortedLLMTasks` uncommitted files are daily job pipeline output (expected). `claude-bot` high restart count is a known pattern. HTTPS push failures are a known workaround situation.\n- **No current failures** -- all repos passing tests, all CI green, no open PRs pending.\n\n---\n\n## Autonomous Dev Progress Log (last 50 lines)\n\nThe log shows Runs 45 and 46 (2026-03-20):\n\n- **Run 45**: runeval received a comprehensive WCAG accessibility pass (PRs #42-#44, auto-merged). Skip-to-content links, ARIA labels, landmark roles, keyboard support across 16+ page files. 129 tests passing, build clean, deployed to staging.\n- **Run 46**: valueSortify received a WCAG accessibility pass (PR #23, auto-merged). Fixed broken keyboard drag handler, added color-blind-friendly labels, list semantics, Escape/click-outside handlers. 38 tests passing, build clean.\n- **Survey note**: All major and mid-tier repos now have WCAG accessibility passes. Only pezantTools remains (server-rendered EJS templates, different approach needed).\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nNothing is broken. All staging services are online with normal restart counts. No failures in the failure log. The autonomous dev agent has been productive, completing accessibility passes on runeval and valueSortify in the last two runs."}],"totalDurationMs":34032,"totalTokens":15229,"totalToolUseCount":5,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4148,"cache_read_input_tokens":10359,"output_tokens":721,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4148},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
